{"FORK":[{"def":"An instrument consisting consisting of a handle with a shank terminating in two or more prongs or tines, which are usually of metal, parallel and slightly curved; -- used from piercing, holding, taking up, or pitching anything.","pos":""},{"def":"Anything furcate or like of a fork in shape, or furcate at the extremity; as, a tuning fork.","pos":""}],"FORK-TAILED":[{"def":"Having the outer tail feathers longer than the median ones; swallow-tailed; -- said of many birds.","pos":""}],"FORKED":[{"def":"Formed into a forklike shape; having a fork; dividing into two or more prongs or branches; furcated; bifurcated; zigzag; as, the forked lighting.","pos":""},{"def":"Having a double meaning; ambiguous; equivocal.","pos":""}],"FORKERVE":[{"def":"See Forcarve, v.","pos":""}],"FORKINESS":[{"def":"The quality or state or dividing in a forklike manner.","pos":""}],"FORKY":[{"def":"Opening into two or more parts or shoots; forked; furcated.","pos":""}]}